  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Preheat oven to 180°C/356°F."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add chicken breasts to a baking tray. Drizzle over some olive oil and a tbsp of soy sauce. Mix everything together. Add the chicken to the oven for 25 minutes until perfectly cooked through."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once cooked, remove the chicken. Shred it with 2 forks and set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Veg prep time. Peel, de-seed and cut your cucumber into slices. Cut your peppers into slices and cube up your avocado. Finely slice your chilli, coriander and basil."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Get your soba noodles on (follow pack instructions). When they are ready, place them in a bowl with cold water so they are cool when you assemble the salad."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Dressing time. Into a jar or bowl, add your olive oil, sesame oil, soy sauce and the juice of a lime. Mix everything together."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serving time. Get a big salad bowl. Add all your elements in to the bowl. Scatter your chopped chilli and herbs on top. Add your dressing. Toss everything together, serve up and enjoy!"
    }
  ],
